{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888192865,"sessionID":"ses_284d0e1caffep8wkYpNE5l4Qze","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2f51bf001M65XeJZEOX72mw","messageID":"msg_d7b2f4637001TBSeyLhU5ehbP6","sessionID":"ses_284d0e1caffep8wkYpNE5l4Qze","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_53e75680313f4851b45f3844","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-043/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-043/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-043 — Architecture Design Documents & API Documentation\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing architecture design documents and API documentation for the agentcube project.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-043\n10: - **Module**: `docs`\n11: - **Language**: Markdown\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Spec**: None (standalone requirement)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Architecture Design Document\n18: \n19: ### AR-043-001: System architecture overview\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a new architecture design requirement\n22: - **WHEN** creating the system architecture document\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL include a high-level system diagram\n24: - **AND** SHALL document the core components (Agent Runtime, Code Interpreter, Router, Workload Manager)\n25: \n26: ### AR-043-002: Component documentation\n27: \n28: - **GIVEN** architecture design document\n29: - **WHEN** documenting each component\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL describe the component's purpose and responsibilities\n31: - **AND** SHALL include component interactions and data flows\n32: \n33: ### AR-043-003: Infrastructure documentation\n34: \n35: - **GIVEN** architecture design document\n36: - **WHEN** documenting infrastructure\n37: - **THEN** it SHALL describe the Kubernetes deployment topology\n38: - **AND** SHALL document the Helm chart structure and configuration\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## Scenario: API Documentation\n43: \n44: ### AR-043-004: SDK client API documentation\n45: \n46: - **GIVEN** agentcube Python SDK\n47: - **WHEN** generating API documentation\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL document the ControlPlaneClient class\n49: - **AND** SHALL document all public methods with parameter types and return values\n50: \n51: ### AR-043-005: REST API endpoints documentation\n52: \n53: - **GIVEN** Workload Manager REST API\n54: - **WHEN** documenting API endpoints\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL document the `/v1/code-interpreter` endpoint\n56: - **AND** SHALL include request/response schemas and HTTP methods\n57: \n58: ### AR-043-006: CLI command documentation\n59: \n60: - **GIVEN** agentcube CLI tool\n61: - **WHEN** documenting CLI commands\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL document all available commands\n63: - **AND** SHALL include usage examples and argument descriptions\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## Scenario: Kubernetes Resources Documentation\n68: \n69: ### AR-043-007: CRD documentation\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** AgentCube custom resource definitions\n72: - **WHEN** documenting CRDs\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL document AgentRuntime CRD schema\n74: - **AND** SHALL document CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n75: \n76: ### AR-043-008: Helm values documentation\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** Helm chart for AgentCube\n79: - **WHEN** documenting Helm values\n80: - **THEN** it SHALL document all configurable values\n81: - **AND** SHALL include default values and descriptions\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## Scenario: Documentation Organization\n86: \n87: ### AR-043-009: Documentation structure\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** documentation project\n90: - **WHEN** organizing documentation\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL follow Docusaurus directory structure\n92: - **AND** SHALL have separate sections for guides, API reference, and architecture\n93: \n94: ### AR-043-010: Documentation navigation\n95: \n96: - **GIVEN** documentation site\n97: - **WHEN** configuring navigation\n98: - **THEN** it SHALL have a clear sidebar with logical grouping\n99: - **AND** SHALL support versioned documentation\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## References\n104: \n105: - AgentCube GitHub: https://github.com/agentcube/agentcube\n106: - Docusaurus: https://docusaurus.io/\n107: - Python Docstring Style: https://sphinx-rtd-tutorial.readthedocs.io/en/latest/docstrings.html\n\n(End of file - total 107 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-043 — Architecture Design Documents & API Documentation\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing architecture design documents and API documentation for the agentcube project.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-043\n- **Module**: `docs`\n- **Language**: Markdown\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Spec**: None (standalone requirement)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Architecture Design Document\n\n### AR-043-001: System architecture overview\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-043/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775888192848,"end":1775888192863}}}}
